✅ Install order (Windows)
Node.js (LTS) – installs Node + npm

Git

PostgreSQL (include pgAdmin in the installer)

Visual Studio Code

Optional (add right after the four above): Postman, DBeaver, Docker Desktop.

▶️ After install: one-time setup & verification
Open PowerShell as Administrator (Win+X → Windows PowerShell (Admin)).

A. Verify tools
powershell
Copy
Edit
node -v
npm -v
git --version
psql --version
B. Git basics (global once)
powershell
Copy
Edit
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
git config --global core.autocrlf true
C. Project folder + base Node setup
powershell
Copy
Edit
# choose a location you like
mkdir C:\VytalGuard && cd C:\VytalGuard

# init git & node
git init
npm init -y
D. Install core npm packages
powershell
Copy
Edit
# prod deps
npm i express sequelize pg pg-hstore cors dotenv jsonwebtoken bcrypt joi multer

# dev deps (tools you’ll use in development)
npm i -D nodemon sequelize-cli